Ignore all the squiggly
lines around it.

00:09:26.825 --> 00:09:31.330
And let me put but both of my
bars in some aqueous solution.

00:09:31.330 --> 00:09:34.310
And there could be some other
dissolved ions in there to

00:09:34.310 --> 00:09:37.630
help neutralize the different--
so I put them both

00:09:37.630 --> 00:09:40.230
in an aqueous solution.

00:09:40.230 --> 00:09:41.480
But they're separate.

00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:49.060
And let me label them
appropriately.

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:55.210
So this is my zinc. Zinc right
here, a bar of solid sync.

00:09:55.210 --> 00:09:57.490
And this is my bar
of solid copper.

00:09:57.490 --> 00:09:58.960
I should do that in
