00:10:04.470 --> 00:10:07.050
So what happens if we
were to connect

00:10:07.050 --> 00:10:08.640
these two metals, right?

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:09.230
They're metals.

00:10:09.230 --> 00:10:10.480
If you look at the periodic
table they're

00:10:10.480 --> 00:10:13.660
both transition metals.

00:10:13.660 --> 00:10:15.570
They both have the
sea of electrons.

00:10:15.570 --> 00:10:17.350
So they both conduct
electricity well.

00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:21.880
What happens if you connect
these two with a wire?

00:10:21.880 --> 00:10:27.370
So if I connect them with a
wire right here like that.

00:10:27.370 --> 00:10:30.780
So we already know that the
zinc is just dying to jump

00:10:30.780 --> 00:10:33.880
into the water and lose
its electrons, right?

00:10:33.880 --> 00:10:36.670
So let's say that happens.

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:40.430
So the zinc jumps into the
aqueous solution, and it turns

00:10:40.430 --> 00:10:44.720
into a positive ion of zinc.
And then its electrons are

00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:47.030
left behind, right?

00:10:47.030 --> 00:10:48.980
So it essentially has
two electrons.

00:10:48.980 --> 00:10:51.300
I did the half reaction
right here, right?

00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:54.410
The zinc jumps into the solution
and it leaves behind

00:10:54.410 --> 00:10:56.850
two electrons right here.

00:10:56.850 --> 00:10:59.810
Two electrons here, they really
want to jump off of the

00:10:59.810 --> 00:11:00.470
zinc.

00:11:00.470 --> 00:11:05.110
Now I have a lot of copper out
of here, out here in the

00:11:05.110 --> 00:11:09.850
solution, that really want to
jump on to this bar of copper.

00:11:09.850 --> 00:11:12.050
But right now they're
all ions.

00:11:12.050 --> 00:11:13.340
These are all plus 2 ions.

00:11:18.350 --> 00:11:20.970
And they really want to jump on
to the bar and join all of

00:11:20.970 --> 00:11:23.190
these other copper ions here.

00:11:23.190 --> 00:11:25.530
But in order to jump
on to that, they

00:11:25.530 --> 00:11:27.880
have to get some electrons.

00:11:27.880 --> 00:11:30.270
Each of these guys have
to grab two electrons.

00:11:30.270 --> 00:11:34.580
And we know that kind
of potential, or the

00:11:34.580 --> 00:11:37.170
